      • HAS_PUBLISHER

        public static final java.lang.String HAS_PUBLISHER
        When this property is enabled, a publisher flow is created when a Transacted Session is created successfully. HAS_PUBLISHER must be enabled if the application intends to publish messages (TransactedSessionHandle.send(com.solacesystems.solclientj.core.handle.MessageHandle))

        Default: ENABLE

        Possible values in SolEnum.BooleanValue

      • REQUESTREPLY_TIMEOUT_MS

        public static final java.lang.String REQUESTREPLY_TIMEOUT_MS
        Timeout (in milliseconds) to wait for a response. The minimum configuration value is 1000.

        Default: 10000 (10 seconds)

        Possible values: greater than or equal to 1000 (1 second)

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • PUB_WINDOW_SIZE

        public static final java.lang.String PUB_WINDOW_SIZE
        Transacted publisher window size, if supported by broker. When connecting to PubSub+ brokers 9.8.1 or later, this property allows the application to reduce the outstanding window if there are memory/resource restrictions that preclude the larger window. For example, if the application is only publishing large or max size messages (30mb), it may wish to restrict the number in flight.

        Range is 1-255

        Default: 255

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
